---
import TextPageLayout from "../../layouts/TextPageLayout.astro";
import {pageMeta} from "../../data/pageMeta";

const meta = pageMeta.pronunciation;
---

<TextPageLayout
        title={meta.title}
        description={meta.description}
        canonicalPath={meta.path}
        ogType={meta.ogType}
>
    <article class="test pronunciation-page">
        <h1>Pronunciation</h1>

        <p class="pronunciation-page__name">Stevan Veljkovic</p>

        <p class="pronunciation pronunciation-page__transcription">
                <span
                        class="pronunciation__ipa"
                        lang="und-fonipa"
                        aria-label="Stevan Veljkovic pronunciation"
                >/ˈstɛv(ə)n ˈvɛl.kə.vɪk/</span>
        </p>

        <p>
            This is the pronunciation of my name in English. The transcription
            is <a
                href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Phonetic_transcription#Narrow_versus_broad;_phonemic_versus_phonetic">broad</a>
            rather than narrowly phonetic.
        </p>

        <p>
            My first name is stressed on the first syllable: <span class="pronunciation__ipa" lang="und-fonipa">/ˈstɛv(ə)n/</span>.
            The first vowel is <span class="pronunciation__ipa" lang="und-fonipa">/ɛ/</span>, the DRESS vowel of
            English, as in <em>bed</em> in many accents. The middle vowel may be reduced.
        </p>

        <p>
            The first syllable is therefore STEV, not STEEV; it is not pronounced like the names Steven and
            Steve.
        </p>

        <p>
            My surname is also stressed on the first syllable: <span class="pronunciation__ipa" lang="und-fonipa">/ˈvɛl.kə.vɪk/</span>.
            In my pronunciation, the middle vowel is reduced.
        </p>

        <p>
            All together, roughly: STEV-(ən) VEL-kuh-vik.
        </p>

        <p>
            Audio may be added later.
        </p>
    </article>
</TextPageLayout>